# The human is the oracle: no AI sits in the verdict path (scope & guarantees §5).
# These paths are flowmap's gated artifacts plus the config and per-flow tests
# that legitimately move their baseline — every change to them routes to a human
# reviewer, who judges "is this the behavior I expect?".
#
# A test-only change (swapping a mock, changing a stub's return) can shift a
# golden with no production-code change; that is a legitimate baseline shift, so
# the per-flow test files are owned here too (consistency pass).

# Gated static artifact: the inter-service boundary contract + blind-spot manifest.
**/.flowmap/boundary-contract.json   @jyang234

# Tier-map / classification config that drives both pipelines.
**/.flowmap.yaml                     @jyang234

# Gated behavioral artifacts: the canonical golden IR and its rendered view.
**/testdata/flows/*.golden.json      @jyang234
**/testdata/flows/*.flow.md          @jyang234

# Gated post-hoc behavioral artifact: the boundary-effect set asserted by
# `flowmap behavior ingest --flows-dir` (no-new-effects gate). Adopters route
# their own --flows-dir path the same way.
**/*.effects.json                    @jyang234

# Per-flow tests: a test change is a deliberate baseline shift, not noise.
**/flows/*_test.go                   @jyang234
